Company description: Book your stay to Tahiti ! Motivated by an intimate knowledge of and affection for French Polynesia (also called the islands of Tahiti), Discover Polynesia invites you to the ultimate travel experience, devoid of gimmicks and blissfully released from mass tourism. With its expertise of Travel Designer, exclusive deals and extensive travel experience, Discover Polynesia is able to design tailored itineraries to fulfill each travel dream. The advantages of delegating to a Travel Designer are multiple: Tahiti is a remote and vast destination that spans on a territory as vast as Europe (a total of 118 islands), so it is almost impossible to coordinate your trip by yourself, contrary to other destinations. Discover Polynesia imagine a realistic and relevant program regarding the profile of travellers (solo, couples, families).  Due to its complexities, the destination of Tahiti and its islands is an "intermediated" destination, in other words with many intermediaries (in the traditional distribution: you book through your preferred travel agency based in your living area > that buys your stay trough a specialized tour operator based in your country > that buys your stay to an inbound travel agency based in Tahiti...). Of course, each intermediary margins the production of your stay. Discover Polynesia allows to reduce the costs of your stay, by removing an intermediary, connecting you directly with the most relevant inbound travel agency.

Company description: Misterlodge is a brand of LODGE AND CO Group. In order not to succumb to the devastating spread of mass tourism, we have decided to offer you an up-to-date selection of the best lodges, ecolodges, bungalows, cabins, gites, carbets, fares, charming hotels and straw huts in the world, accommodation that respects nature and its inhabitants, away from the crowds. Thus, you will gradually have access to accommodation that respects the environment and its inhabitants, where simplicity is luxury. Admittedly, our selection of accommodation is sometimes positioned in the middle-upper end of the market and can be more expensive, but it is preferable to enhance the appreciation of a trip by individualizing it rather than to distort local life through a massive infiltration of tourists; some destinations are revising their "tourism" policy in order to preserve their culture and environment, and also realize the negative impact of flat rental platforms when no limits are set. Not so long ago, in the value chain of a trip, air transport was the most expensive; today, this is often no longer the case with the arrival of low-cost airlines. Some low fare airlines are standardizing to long-haul destinations, and deeply traditional airlines are tending to reduce their costs by changing their business model on short- and medium-haul flights. It is already possible to travel in low cost - low fare within 5 to 6 hours from home, and therefore to invest more in the land part of the journey. Thus, the organisation of land-based travel becomes the key element of the trip, particularly with the emergence and know-how of local experts ( local tour operators and guides). With our partners, we continue to supply the world's most beautiful lodges, and ecolodges of the Planet and we thank you warmly for your many expressions of support.  Special thanks to our 200,000 unique visitors during this difficult period which affects us all. Jean Michel Bohn

Daniel who had studied in Oxford and Paris, and Sam Blyth of Blyth and Company of Toronto, a student travel agency, the program was coordinated by Douglas Parker, professor of English and former Dean of Humanities, from 1987 until 1992, and then by K.
